The President sends his best wishes to those celebrating Polish Constitution Day. He acknowledges the challenges and tragedies the Polish people have faced but also recognizes their perseverance and their inspirational role in the world. He mentions that Poland is seen as an example and guide for democratic movements. The President also emphasizes the importance of Polish Americans in the United States and highlights the partnership between the United States and Poland in promoting stability, security, and economic opportunity globally. He expresses his anticipation for strengthening the ties between the two countries during his upcoming visit to Warsaw.